C:\Data\Nucleus_Dev\Vostok_ACU_A\source\XCategory\Hbl\all\LLIHandler\I2CRHTSensorLLI\I2CRHTSensorLLI.c
      1          /**
      2           *  @file       I2CRHTSensorLLI.c
      3           *
      4           *  @brief      Basic description of file contents
      5           *
      6           *  @details    Detailed description of the file contents
      7           *              Design Consideration :
      8           *              1) Automic Reading :- TO read every one temperature/humidity reading it takes 1000 millisecond.
      9           *                 This Time need to be considered while designing the GI module
     10           *              2) This module handles only one device can be configured to read either temperature or Humidity or both Temperature and humidity value.
     11           *              3) Minimum Sampling rate to read One sensor value shall not be less then 100ms
     12           *              4) When more then one sensor is enabled on the same bus the handler will always service the first requested sensor only
     13           *  	 	 	   as per Hbl architecture (I2C read/Write commands are processed in 1ms handler)
     14           *  	 	 	   In order to avoid the conjunction on the I2C bus we will be processing the one sensor data at a time
     15           *
     16           *
     17           *
     18           *  	 	 	Special Design Consideration SHT2X :
     19           *  	 	 	    It is been observed that SHT2X I2C device gives wrong reading after few hours of operation or
     20           *  	 	 	    fluctuation of reading value with difference of more then 2 C for temperature and 10 % for Humidity
     21           *  	 	 	    Due to which the SHT2x Device needs to be Reset
     22           *  	 	 	    Resets are done on the below Conditions :
     23           *  	 	 	    i)   Reset After every 6 hours  Or
     24           *  	 	 	    ii)  Reset if the Delta observed between current reading and previous reading more then 2 C  or
     25           *  	 	 	    iii) Reset if the Delta observed between current reading and previous reading more then 10 % Humidity
     26           *
     27           *  	 	 	    i) On Power up do not monitor the reset condition and take the reading up to 1 minute
     28           *  	 	 	    ii) Do not take the reading for 1 minute once the device is reseted, up to this 1 minute publish the previous correct reading
     29           *
     30           *
     31           * @section    Applicable_Documents
     32           *					List here all the applicable documents if needed. <tr>	
     33           *
     34           *  $Header: $
     35           *
     36           *  @copyright  Copyright 2017-$Date$. Whirlpool Corporation. All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL
     37           */
